MATCH_TOOL: Bash
MATCH_PATTERN: (lsof.*-i.*:(5173|8787|3000)|npm run dev|wrangler dev( |$))
ADVISORY: |
  Heads up: this monorepo uses git worktrees (.worktrees/*). If a dev server is
  already running from a DIFFERENT worktree than the one you're editing in, your
  source changes will appear to have no effect (Vite cache buster timestamp won't
  update, HMR seems silent, behavior matches old code).

  Always verify before debugging:
    lsof -i :5173 :8787 :3000 | grep LISTEN
    lsof -p <pid> | grep cwd

  The `cwd` line shows the directory the process is serving from. If it's not the
  canonical pecking-order dir (or not your active branch's worktree), kill the
  processes and restart `npm run dev` from the right location.

  Real session cost: ~30 min lost in the Pulse shell work debugging code that
  was never being delivered to the browser.
